The adidas Yeezy line by Kanye West is one of the brand's most creative and most popular. This iconic collaboration began in 2015 after West left Nike. See More
After taking some time to make the initial designs, the "Yeezy Season 1" collaboration between the artist and the company debuted. Many felt that Yeezys displayed more of the creative freedom they'd come to expect from Kanye than any of his previous collaborations had. The Yeezy 750 was the first sneaker the team collaborated on, and it featured suede upper layers, straps, and zippers up the back. One of the best aspects of Yeezy shoes is the huge variety of styles and colors available. High-tops, reflective materials, and low-tops are just a few of the different features that sneakerheads can choose when it comes to Yeezys. The overall popularity of these sneakers drives a thriving Yeezy supply market and has fans of Kanye and high-quality shoes looking for rare or limited models. The colorful Yeezy Boost 350 v2s dropped at the end of 2019.
